quotes.quote: It was a lovely performance. Don Pacifico put that experience at Wolverhampton to good use and I was very comfortable once I got him relaxed and in a rhythm. He's still inexperienced and had a look around in the straight so hopefully there's more to come- Jack Mitchell, jockey, speaking on Sky Sports Racing.

runners.owner: Two Plus Three Two Plus Four

stable_tour.quote: He's a fun sprinter who goes round Chester well. He was probably beaten by the draw on his second start since being gelded at Southwell last month but there are more races to win with him. He had a terrible draw last time but ran perfectly well. The key thing is he's qualified to run at Lingfield on Good Friday. 09-04-25

runners.breeder: S A R L Al Shira'Aa Farms

stable_tour.quote: She's for the same owners as Queues Likely and I think she's going to be very good. I think she'll definitely end up a black-type filly, most likely over a mile or seven furlongs. I was pleased with the way she ran at Bath because I thought she'd run a nice race as she'd been working lovely at home. Her half-brother was second in the Brocklesby and was sold to America straight away after that. He has run well in a big race in America and it's going to end up quite a nice page. She's got the size and scope. 04-07-24

racecards.race_name: Fitzdares Sprint Series Qualifier Handicap (Windsor Sprint Series Qualifier)

runners.owner: P Merritt, K Lawrence & P Cook

quotes.race: Boost Your Acca At BetMGM Handicap
quotes.quote: Havanagreattime can be really strong when he has something taking him on but, when he relaxes in front and gets an easy lead, he's a different horse and he really quickened up well down that hill. We've always liked him and we thought he'd win a few more but hopefully next year he could turn out to be decent - Finley Marsh, jockey, speaking on Sky Sports Racing.

quotes.race: William Hill Extra Place Races Handicap
quotes.quote: Durham Castle is quite a big horse. You'd hope everything he does this year should help him improve next year. These sprint handicaps are quite competitive and there are some well-seasoned horses in there, so I thought he did very well. He's very straightforward and he followed a strong pace there. He got a nice tow into the race, he built into it lovely, and he finished off strong. I thought there's a chance he'll get another furlong - William Buick, jockey, speaking to Racing TV.

quotes.race: Read Harry Cobden's Blog At Planet Sport Bet Handicap
quotes.quote: Al Barez was push-button to ride and I loved his attitude. He didn't win very far but I probably got there early enough because the pace collapsed - Oisin Murphy, jockey.

quotes.race: Virgin Bet Best Odds Daily Handicap (London Sprint Series Qualifier)
quotes.quote: Jack did well from that draw and it's nice to get a win on the board. The turf season is around the corner so I hope Al Barez is shaping up well for some nice handicaps this summer. He's still quite an unexposed horse and has a lovely pedigree - Tom Clover, trainer.

stable_tour.quote: He's a lovely horse and it was great to see him run well at Wolverhampton the other day after losing his form through the winter. He looks really well and he'll go to Windsor next. Hopefully he can carry on improving and win plenty of races. 14-05-25

runners.owner: Suman Hedge Bs, Woodside Bs & D Redvers

stable_tour.quote: He was a very good two-year-old but unfortunately he got cast one Sunday afternoon and shattered his pin bone. His pin bone is about four inches down his leg and we were lucky not to lose him. If he hadn't done that he'd have been a very good horse, and it's taken a  few years for him to get going again really but he's back in good from again now, winning the sprint qualifier at Windsor last week. He can be difficult to get on in the paddock, but changing the chute at Windsor to a new entrance further around the bend has made it easier for us to mount him, which is why we go back to Windsor as much as we can. He'll run in the sprint final there on August 12 all being well. He was a close fourth in it last year, but he's in better form this year. 11-07-24

This colt was extremely well bought at the Deauville breeze-up and after some encouraging work he made a lovely start at Newbury when third to Sketch over 6f. I think that was a nice race and he came out of it well. I sent him to Salisbury last week for his second run and he ran very well for a long way before tiring in the final furlong. He's better than that and will be winning sooner rather than later. 17-08-23

It's nice to have another horse for Anthony Hogarth and his wife Val, who have been owners here before. The dam of this colt has three black-type winners from three foals - Trillium, Mohawk King and American Kestrel - and hopefully he can make it four from four. He's going well and should be ready to go next month. I'm looking to start him off over 5f. 19-04-23

racecards.race_name: Call Fitzdares For Top Prices Restricted Novice Stakes (For horses In Bands C And D) (GBB Race)

stable_tour.quote: He ran just once last year but has been showing up well at home and will be out in the next fortnight or so. 22-04-25

runners.breeder: Kirtlington Park, A Davis & E Foster

racecards.race_name: Fitzdares Taking Bets Since 1882 EBF Restricted Maiden Stakes (Band D) (EBF Rest' Qual') (GBB Race)

runners.owner: John & Peter Seabrook And Tim Fisher
The Upt North Darn South Syndicate
Mrs J Woods R P Gallagher & Partner

prev_owners.owner: Mrs J Woods R P Gallagher & Partner

racecards.race_name: Join Fitzdares For A Personal Service Handicap
Midlands National On 11th July (Pro/Am) Flat Race

runners.breeder: J L Couetil & Mme J L Couetil

runners.owner: J J Leckey & Donal P Keane & P J Rothwell

racecards.race_name: Belvedere House & Gardens Galway Plate Trial Handicap Chase

quotes.race: Belvedere House & Gardens Opportunity Beginners Chase
quotes.quote: He was a bit novicey over the first couple but Ashdale Bob got into a rhythm and saw it out well. He was always going to stay going, I'm not sure if the ones in front did too much. He has schooled really well and I thin he'll be better again when stepped up in distance - Conor Smithers, jockey, speaking to Racing TV.

quotes.race: Colm Quinn BMW Novice Hurdle (Grade 2)
quotes.quote: Robbie (Power) said it was pure class that got him through it. He's grown a lot since Christmas. He's only turned six this year and is starting to fill his frame. He's going to be a lovely horse next season. We'll have a chat with mum and the owners but I'd imagine we'll leave it at that and he could be a really exciting horse going over a fence next year - Kate Harrington, assistant trainer.

quotes.race: BetVictor Make Your Best Bet Novice Hurdle (Grade 2)
quotes.quote: Ashdale Bob was very good. It was important to get him switched off and he switched off lovely. He improved a lot from the last day and I think he'll improve again for some nicer ground, I was impressed with the way he picked up on ground which was a bit dead for him. He's a nice prospect and I think he will step up to 3m without difficulty - Paddy Kennedy, rider

quotes.race: Irish Stallion Farms EBF Maiden Hurdle
quotes.quote: He was tough. He'll come on from that run as well. He was entitled to do that on some of his runs last year. His last run was disappointing but he'd just been a bit weak. He has strengthened up well and he's a nice horse going forward. He jumps very well, he's a chaser in the making and whatever he does over hurdles is a bonus - Paddy Kennedy, rider of Ashdale Bob

stable_tour.quote: He's about three weeks off a run. He surprised me last year because we always knew he wanted very soft ground but then he ran blinders to win at Fairyhouse and finish second in a Grade 1 at Punchestown on nicer ground. He had a tendency to be keen but when he relaxed he was very good. With another summer under his belt, we think we'll see a more professional horse over fences this term. I think he'll start off in a 2m4f beginners' chase and I wouldn't be in a rush to step him up to three miles. He could develop into a good novice. 29-10-21

He had a productive autumn, winning back-to-back races including a Grade 2 hurdle over 2m4f. He was down the field behind Gaillard Du Mesnil last time in the Grade 1 Nathaniel Lacy & Partners Novice Hurdle at Leopardstown but that wasn't his true running. He's a smart horse but not among my Cheltenham team this week. 17-03-21

quotes.race: Follow Kilbeggan On Instagram Beginners Chase
quotes.quote: Marv Michael schooled super at home and he's always been a very good jumper. Even in his runs over hurdles we were hoping that chasing would bring a bit of improvement and hopefully that's the case - Robbie Power, stable representative.

quotes.race: Tramore Amusements Maiden Hurdle
quotes.quote: Marv Michael is really improving and I'd say the cheekpieces helped him. He seemed in mighty form coming here and we were happy with him. He was beaten by what is probably a nice horse at Wexford and he was unlucky not to win at Down Royal last year, so he has good form - Henry de Bromhead, trainer

stable_tour.quote: He won his maiden hurdle at Galway quite emphatically, but never went a yard at Tramore. He's better than that and hopefully we'll get him back on track soon. 28-10-24

quotes.race: Tipperary Town Plate Handicap Chase
quotes.quote: Good As Hell was able to dictate and got a good ride from Niall. She needed a good jump at the last and nearly gave it away but she got back on an even keel. She will hopefully make a good broodmare down the line - Philip Fenton, trainer.

quotes.race: Tipperary Town Plate Handicap Chase
quotes.quote: Good As Hell is a great servant and hopefully can progress. We're only learning about her best trip. She'll have a little break now and hopefully will turn up in Listowel - Philp Fenton, trainer.

quotes.race: Tipperary Racecourse Handicap Chase
quotes.quote: She just does enough but Good As Hell is a serious mare to jump, she's always making ground at her fences. She's a nice mare to have and I'm sure there will be more fun to be had with over the summer - Niall Moore, jockey, talking to Racing TV

quotes.race: Tipperary Handicap Chase
quotes.quote: Good As Hell might hold her own in this company and she will have one more run as she has been on the go for a while - Philip Fenton, trainer.

runners.owner: Mark R D Fleming / T Westropp Bennett

quotes.race: Ballygowan Opportunity Maiden Hurdle
quotes.quote: Gaelic Arc is a funny horse, difficult to train, and a horse you wouldn't have a punt on. He's going to be a lovely horse over a fence. The ground today probably suited him and was the key today. Niall Prendergast gave him a cracking ride and he'll go over fences now - John Ryan, trainer.

quotes.race: BetVictor INH Flat Race
quotes.quote: Gaelic Arc is a gorgeous horse. He goes on soft ground so we'll probably go for a winners bumper - John Ryan, trainer

quotes.race: Co-Op Superstores Handicap Chase (Listed Race)
quotes.quote: We were hoping Typical Thomas would run well, but we'd have been delighted had he finished in the first four beforehand. With the ground drying out and off the light weight, we were quietly confident - James Andrew Fahey, trainer.

quotes.race: Moyvalley Meats Beginners Chase
quotes.quote: Typical Thomas was very lucky. I was worried that Downpatrick might have taken a bit out of him but we had to take our chance. He will get a little break now - James Fahey, trainer.

stable_tour.quote: He has the makings of a nice enough stayer. The ground was just too soft for him at Listowel last month and he didn't handle it. 28-10-24

quotes.race: K-Mech Mechanical Handicap Chase
quotes.quote: That's Hardwired's third win around Punchestown and he's won five now with five different jockeys. He gave him a great ride and is some value for 3lb. He didn't travel well and was hunting him several times. He's a tricky ride and a hard horse to win on - Ted Walsh, trainer.

quotes.race: Kilberry Handicap Chase
quotes.quote: In fairness Hardwired stayed at it well. He looked beat going to the last, but kept at it well. He's won over 2m6f and three miles, and he saw it out well. From being a frustrating horse he's now won four. He had a good pilot on board - Ted Walsh, trainer.

quotes.race: Race In Pink Handicap Hurdle
quotes.quote: El Champo was back in trip here which was ideal as he was able to roll on in front. That race was made for him. He was let dictate and that really suits around here. He might go chasing now - Philip Rothwell, trainer

quotes.race: Tom Lynam Memorial Handicap Hurdle
quotes.quote: El Champo is a lovely horse. He had run well in a couple of maidens that worked out well and I hoped he could be competitive. He could go straight to a beginners chase now - Philip Rothwell, trainer.

quotes.race: SANSERV Rated Novice Chase
quotes.quote: Pakens Rock is a small horse, is hardly 16 hands and is such a little battler. In those heavy conditions you wouldn't think you'd see a small light framed horse like him but he did it well and loves it here - Barry Murphy, trainer

quotes.race: MansionBet Watch And Bet Beginners Chase
quotes.quote: It's a welcome tonic at this time of the year. He was a bit green the first couple of days in his jumping and we could be a bit more aggressive on him towards the front when he had that experience behind him. He loves this place and has been kept busy over the last few months. We'll stick to the novice route now and decide where we're going next after we know he's in good shape tomorrow morning - Barry Murphy, trainer of Pakens Rock

quotes.race: Matty Ryan Memorial Handicap Hurdle
quotes.quote: Things didn't go right for him the last day in a highly-competitive handicap. We let him freshen up a bit and changed his training routine at home, so we thought he had a good chance coming here. We're almost caught in a hard place with him, we're not in the bottom and not in the top. We'll have to pick our races. That's why I went for a big handicap last time, I thought if we ever had a chance in one of those races it was then because if you win a race like today you go up 6lb and carry that in a big handicap. He's such a tough horse and I think he'd probably get three miles, but I honestly believe he'd win on the Flat. He's not short of a gear, some of his pieces of work are very good - Barry Murphy, trainer of Pakens Rock

quotes.race: Faber Audiovisuals Rated Novice Hurdle
quotes.quote: He did it well and we'd hope he'll stay improving. We're learning a few tricks in how to train him. He's been in very good form for the last while and he improved from last time - I think he knew he had won. The fact that we're coming to a local track and that it's only in the road is a help to him too, it doesn't take that much stress out of him. You have to keep him quiet and calm. We'll get over this first before making plans, I'm full up and have a big yard to think about - two horses! - Barry Murphy, trainer of Pakens Rock

quotes.race: Kenny Developments Maiden Hurdle
quotes.quote: The change in tactics was a help. We went back to the old tactics like at Ballinrobe, keeping him up there fighting. He jumped quite well. I'd imagine we'll have to head down the novice road, we won't aim too high yet. He's a nice horse but the big guns have to come out yet. We'll hope to sneak something somewhere along the way. I think with the ease in the ground, the drop in trip and hill helped - Barry Murphy, trainer of Pakens Rock

racecards.race_name: Follow Kilbeggan On Facebook Beginners Chase

quotes.race: Jack Richards Novices' Limited Handicap Chase (Grade 2) (Registered As The Golden Miller) (GBB Race)
quotes.quote: Anyway ran a cracker. I didn't think he would be that price. His novice chase runs, apart from one, were very good and they were in good company. We knew he was tough and ready for today, but he just ran into a good one. He toughed it out, but he probably wanted it a little bit better. That was my first runner here. It is great to get here, never mind getting into second place so hopefully we will be back. Davy [Russell] is friendly with the owners and he has been riding him out all week. Davy plans the races for him and it is up to me to get them ready. We had little bits here and there on him as he was a great price each-way. He is a summer horse, but we will get over this and see where we go next. It might sound stupid, but I thought we would be there. I know my horse and his ability. I would have been disappointed if he wasn't in the first five - Ken Budds, trainer.

quotes.race: Adare Manor Opportunity Series Final Handicap Hurdle
quotes.quote: Harsh like a big field and I thought he won well. The hustle and bustle suited him, he travelled and jumped great - Joseph O'Brien, trainer

quotes.race: Keith Lynch Memorial Maiden Hurdle
quotes.quote: Maidenstreetprince had a good run the last day and was getting a few pounds today. He was a bit free and there is room for improvement in his jumping. He stuck it out well. We'll see what the handicapper does - Charles Byrnes, trainer.

runners.owner: Jeffrey Brennan & John Cawley & Natalie Gilligan

stable_tour.quote: This guy won a Kelso bumper for Rose Dobbin. We liked that performance and he's a nice looking young horse. He'll be out in a maiden hurdle soon, probably starting off over two miles. 24-10-23

quotes.race: Midsummer's Day With The Stars On Sunday, 23rd June Handicap Hurdle
quotes.quote: West Away got a very good ride from Dylan and it was good to reward him. He has developed into a good horse. He had been running in good quality races for the grade so it was great to win one. He could go to Cartmel for a big pot - John McConnell, trainer.

quotes.race: Racing Again June 4th (Pro/Am) INH Flat Race
quotes.quote: You Oughta Know is not particularly a horse for this track, he probably wants a more galloping track. We went a real strong gallop and it was a messy race. Everyone who rode him at home liked him but he wasn't the sharpest workhorse so we didn't think he'd do what he did but a strong gallop really played into his hands - Patrick Mullins, rider

stable_tour.quote: He disappointed towards the end of last season. We gave him a break, but he's back now and goes novice hurdling. 25-11-24

quotes.race: Cork & Waterford Mares' Point-To-Point Flat Race
quotes.quote: Belle The Lioness was really good. She was keen at home and it was just about getting her to switch off today and learn. She switched off, I could get into the race whenever I wanted and she quickened on down the straight. She was still green and was pricking her ears - Davy Roche, rider.

stable_tour.quote: We'll go back to two miles with her, I'd imagine. She ran okay at Wexford on Friday but I thought she might go a bit closer. We'll probably try fences with her sooner rather than later. 20-11-23

She won a Cork bumper by five lengths on her only start last season. This season she had a couple of good seconds over hurdles and then got her head in front last time at Thurles. Each of her defeats was strong form and her recent run shows she's progressive. She'll go for the Ryanair Mares' Novices' Hurdle at Cheltenham. 01-03-23

racecards.race_name: Paul & Carmel Fay Memorial Handicap Hurdle

runners.owner: Anthony N Durkan & B M Durkan

prev_owners.owner: Anthony N Durkan & B M Durkan
Anthony N Durkan & B M Durkan

quotes.race: John Dowling Memorial Maiden Hurdle
quotes.quote: Topgun Simmy is a lovely horse but I was just a bit worried about the jump up in trip. Paddy gave him a great ride as he didn't panic and gave him a chance. We'll plan something for Galway - Shark Hanlon, trainer.

stable_tour.quote: This chap is a very nice horse. He ran a cracker at Galway in a hot bumper and had bumped into Brighterdaysahead before that at Fairyhouse. That form isn't working out too bad. He might run in a bumper at Leopardstown over Christmas. 27-11-23

quotes.race: Clonmel Oil Service Station Handicap Hurdle
quotes.quote: I suppose Plains Indian was the class horse in the race being a Listed winner and I know he has been disappointing but the ground was too soft for him all year - Willie Slattery, stable representative.

quotes.race: Dunraven Arms Hotel Novice Hurdle (Listed Race)
quotes.quote: Even though his dam is a half-sister to Death Duty I was worried about his stamina because he had been free. I left riding instructions up to Danny and he said there was a good enough pace and Plains Indian settled well. He was off for two years but is back now. I was planning to go for a big handicap at Leopardstown but that's probably gone - Andy Slattery, trainer.

quotes.race: McHale Pro Glide Hurdle
quotes.quote: Plains Indian is an impressive horse and hopefully there is a bit of improvement to come yet. I knew going down to the last I was cantering everywhere so once we got over it he hit the ground running - Cian Quirke, jockey.

quotes.race: Fourmilewater Maiden Hurdle
quotes.quote: Plains Indian had a good confidence booster there and he's a fair horse. As long as the ground isn't too quick he'll probably stay going - Andy Slattery, trainer.

quotes.race: Bet In-Play On Racing With BetVictor Novices' Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
quotes.quote: I was worried mid-race we'd brought I Love My Baie back in trip too much. He's a three miler, but bombed last time, although it wasn't the trip - he just didn't run well. We've given him time to get over that and he's quite a nice horse; he was third in a Listed race at Haydock in November - Anthony Bromley, racing manager for Simon Munir and Isaac Souede.

stable_tour.quote: He's still a nice prospect over hurdles as he only won his maiden hurdle in May. He was progressive through the summer and hopefully he can continue on an upward curve when he returns. 28-10-24

quotes.race: Support The Irish Injured Jockeys Fund Hurdle
quotes.quote: Chinx Of Light is a pure stayer, he just gallops and needed to stay there. I was delighted to see him tough it out and it was good to see him come through a battle. We might go chasing with him but we'll keep him rolling - John McConnell, trainer.

quotes.race: Club Orange Hurdle
quotes.quote: My heart was in my mouth when Chinx Of Light hit the second last. I don't think he ever went as fast to a hurdle in his life. He's a funny sort of a horse, he's very quiet in the stable yard and still has a lot left to develop mentally in his races. He showed a lot of ability there, the way he quickened from the third last to the second last was very impressive - John McConnell, trainer.

stable_tour.quote: He hasn't taken to chasing the way we wanted - he's a light horse who isn't huge - and we might go back hurdling. He's had a break and could be one for the Pertemps or a big staying handicap hurdle like that. He's got a big engine and gallops all day. 21-11-22

quotes.race: Citipost Novices' Hurdle (GBB Race)
quotes.quote: The Friday Man is only a novice for a little while so we said we'd take our chance. He'll go jumping fences now and he's not a bad horse. He'll be a nice chaser - Gordon Elliott, trainer.

quotes.race: Kilbarry (Ladies Pro/Am) Flat Race
quotes.quote: The Friday Man really handled the track, he went around those bends immensely. He tried coming up the hill and found plenty - Lisa O'Neill, jockey.

stable_tour.quote: He's been a great money-spinner though the summer and has won four times in the space of a few months. He'll go for a Graded novice hurdle at Limerick next. He's progressing with every run. 18-10-22

quotes.race: Racing Again December 21st Mares Handicap Hurdle
quotes.quote: The rain really helped Ad Caelum and she's an exciting mare for the future. Sean really fancied her and I was a bit concerned as she likes to get her toe in, but the ground has gone yielding which helped. She'll need soft ground and should be progressive in handicaps, or she could go to a rated novice hurdle - John Ryan, trainer, speaking to Racing TV.

quotes.race: Adare Manor Opportunity Handicap Hurdle
quotes.quote: Billy Lee Swagger gurgled all the way up the straight. I probably had the wrong bit in his mouth as he'd never done it before. I was really happy with him and he was working really well. The day he was fourth in the maiden hurdle at Gowran was a good run and I thought he'd go on the ground here - Philip Rothwell, trainer.

quotes.race: Irish Stallion Farms EBF Mares Maiden Hurdle
quotes.quote: I probably took a bit of a risk running Long Gone back over this trip but it was a 15 grand race and you've the bonus too so Gilmer (Bates, owner) said to take a chance. We got a little bit of luck on the day with the two fallers. We'll look to step up in trip now for a novice. Ideally, she'd want two miles four and five. She showed a good attitude and stayed, she was flat out the whole way - Declan Queally, trainer.

racecards.race_name: Belvedere House & Gardens Handicap Hurdle (Div II)

quotes.race: BetVictor Rated Novice Hurdle
quotes.quote: The Little Yank had a lot of trouble with ulcers and we couldn't figure what was wrong with him. He's going to be a smashing chaser for the summer - John Ryan, trainer.

runners.breeder: S C E A Ecurie Biraben

racecards.race_name: Belvedere House & Gardens Handicap Hurdle (Div I)

runners.breeder: E A R L Ecurie Des Mottes

quotes.race: Your New Tote At Limerick Racecourse Handicap Hurdle
quotes.quote: Rebellious Gale ran well last time and that trip [one mile and seven furlongs] around Kilbeggan was probably sharp enough for him. I'd say the track sharpened him up, though, as he had been lacklustre. He's pulled it all together today and hopefully will progress from that - Peter Carberry, rider.

runners.breeder: M Goulven, Mlle Celine, M Pierre-Yves Berthouloux & Mme Fa
runners.owner: Profit In Your Pocket Racing Club

racecards.race_name: Watch Every Race Live On Racing TV (Q.R.) Maiden Hurdle

runners.owner: Treaty Retail Invest' Holdings Ltd/Denis Murphy B'stock Ltd
John P Coleman & M J Caffrey

runners.breeder: Mme Marion Marteau & E A R L Haras De La Bouloye

racecards.race_name: Follow Kilbeggan On Instagram Mares Hurdle

stable_tour.quote: She won a mares' maiden hurdle well at Sligo over the summer and would have gone close to winning at Perth had she not come down at the last. I can see her winning a novice hurdle. 28-10-24

She's on a break now and will come back in the spring. She was very green in her first couple of runs but was really good the other day when winning at Cork. It might be a bit ambitious but I'd like to aim her towards the mares' novice hurdle at Cheltenham. She's owned by a great bunch and they never shirk a trip. 18-11-24
